 Determine the value of each limit. If a two-sided limit does not exist, determine each one-sided limit. If a limit is infinite, state whether it is positive or negative infinity and describe the associated function behavior. 



\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
\item \[\lim_{ t\to2 }\frac{t - 2}{\sqrt{t + 23} - 5}\]
\item \[\lim_{ h\to6 }\frac{h^{2} - 8 \, h + 15}{h^{2} + 2 \, h - 24}\]
\item \[\lim_{ h\to-1 }\frac{h^{2} + 7 \, h + 6}{h^{2} + 6 \, h + 5}\]
\item \[\lim_{ h\to2 }\frac{h^{2} + 4 \, h + 4}{h^{2} - 3 \, h + 2}\]
\end{enumerate}

     \end{exerciseStatement}
 \begin{exerciseAnswer} 

\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
\item \(10\)
\item \(\frac{1}{8}\)
\item \(\frac{5}{4}\)
\item 

The limit does not exist.



\begin{itemize}
\item \[\lim_{ h\to2^- }\frac{h^{2} + 4 \, h + 4}{h^{2} - 3 \, h + 2} = -\infty\]
\item \[\lim_{ h\to2^+ }\frac{h^{2} + 4 \, h + 4}{h^{2} - 3 \, h + 2} = +\infty\]
\item 

The graph of the function \(f(h)=\frac{h^{2} + 4 \, h + 4}{h^{2} - 3 \, h + 2}\) has a vertical asymptote at \(h=2\).


\end{itemize}


\end{enumerate}

     \end{exerciseAnswer}
 \end{exercise}

