\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
\item  

 Determine the value of the given limit. If the limit is infinite, state whether it is positive or negative infinity. 

 \[\lim_{x\to+\infty } -\frac{2 \, {\left(3 \, x^{3} + 2 \, x\right)}}{x^{4} - 7 \, x^{2} - 4 \, x}\] 
\item  

 Determine all horizontal asympototes of the given function. If the function has no horizontal asymptotes, describe the end behavior of the function. Use limits to justify your answer. 

 \[f(x) = -\frac{\sqrt{x^{10}} + 3}{2 \, {\left(3 \, x^{4} + x^{2}\right)}}\] 
\end{enumerate}

     \end{exerciseStatement}
 \begin{exerciseAnswer} 

\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
\item \(0\)
\item  

The function \(f(x)\) has no horizontal asymptotes. The end behavior of \(f(x)\) is as follows:



\begin{itemize}
\item \(\lim_{x\to-\infty}-\frac{\sqrt{x^{10}} + 3}{2 \, {\left(3 \, x^{4} + x^{2}\right)}} = -\infty\).
\item \(\lim_{x\to+\infty}-\frac{\sqrt{x^{10}} + 3}{2 \, {\left(3 \, x^{4} + x^{2}\right)}} = -\infty\).
\end{itemize}


\end{enumerate}

     \end{exerciseAnswer}
 \end{exercise}

